<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-0743CE4B-4B8E-4315-889B-B4B37348F19F" version="3" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-0743CE4B-4B8E-4315-889B-B4B37348F19F" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">02 The function of the ink tubes and pumps</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The system uses pumps to pump the ink from the ink tanks through the ink tubes to the printheads. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Overview</title><table id="GUID-44CC9D37-524C-4240-A579-9C6FC3D85313" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Function 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink tube 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Every ink tank has two connections (C). One of the ink tubes is towards the ink pump. The other ink tube is blocked (not used). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Each connection goes to a separate pump. 
</p><fig id="FIG_882FB683084849C3887A4D313DF30CD9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6DF11D08-DE5E-4E5F-83B7-C664CBFCD8F9-low.png" id="IMAGE_3149681947A1466282B865276D6B6EBD" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6DF11D08-DE5E-4E5F-83B7-C664CBFCD8F9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink pump 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The pumps pump the ink from the ink tank to one of the printhead (s). The ink system from the ink tank to the printhead is a closed system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The ink pump uses a peristaltic principle to pump the ink from the ink tank to the printhead (s). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The ink tube (pump tube) in the pump is flexible. A set of rollers inside the pump squeezes the pump tube and the ink inside the tube is pushed forward towards the printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For detailed information see : 
<xref href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peristaltic_pump" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peristaltic_pump</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Electrical diagram ink delivery See: 
<xref keyref="02ELEC01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-75F92436-156E-4A46-B4B2-21D436EB31B2.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 Electrical diagram ink delivery?>02 Electrical diagram ink delivery</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Each ink tank has 1 pump connected. 
</p><fig id="GUID-07C3EF46-21E1-4856-B7D2-2C0AB5E4A0E0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-761D7F76-9349-48B7-B90B-6810C56DA0C5-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-761D7F76-9349-48B7-B90B-6810C56DA0C5-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">In the drawing you see all 5 pumps: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Ink system pump 2 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 02M1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">INK_PUMP_2_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Ink system pump 3 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 02M3 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">INK_PUMP_3_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Ink system pump 4 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 02M5 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">INK_PUMP_4_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Ink system pump 5 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 02M7 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">INK_PUMP_5_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Ink system pump 6 motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 02M50 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">INK_PUMP_6_MO</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">For example pump 02M7 is used to pump the black ink (K). All pumps are connected to the ink tanks directly beneath it. You can see the ink tubes leaving towards the printheads on the right hand side. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You can see that the tube inside the pumps has a different color. This is a different and flexible type of tube. To be able to use the peristaltic principle you need a flexible ink tube. The regular black ink tube is too hard and inflexible to be used there. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See also: 
<xref keyref="mapprintheads" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-67370C7B-66D6-4187-925F-34D9A20977DB.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Mapping pumps to printheads?>Mapping pumps to printheads</xref>
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-FE35F538-1785-4DC7-A246-E1EB5ED33BE7.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>